Introduction

Five Run Strike (Korean: 파이브런스트라이크; Japanese: ファイブランストライク) also known as SKIREN (スカイレン) were a short lived 4 member Korean rock/indie band under Rover Entertainment.

The line up consisted of ACE, Rami, Myoungshin and JK. The fifth person in the debut MV was their drummer and was not a permanent member. While the fifth person in the picture above they only played the drums during live stages.

They debuted with their single "can you hear me?" On July 21st 2016. In February 2017 Myoungshin departed from the group and the group rebranded as SKIREN. They disbanded later in 2017.

One of their drummers name was CHO.
